President Biden convened the Global COVID-19 Summit to discuss ending the pandemic and building better global health security. He called on leaders to take urgent action and cooperate to respond to the crisis. World leaders embraced a set of ambitious global targets across four themes. President Biden announced new U.S. commitments, including vaccinating the world, saving lives now, and building back better. All countries and organizations must play their part in taking urgent actions. The United States will champion accountability and measure progress against shared targets. The Secretary of State will convene foreign ministers to update on progress and maintain global urgency to end the pandemic in 2022.